Look upon a little child;
Pity my simplicity,
Suffer me to come to thee

Lamb of God, I look to Thee;
Thou shalt my example be;
Thou art gentle, meek and mild;
Thou was once a little child

Fain I would be as thou art;
Give me Thy obedient heart;
Thou art pitiful and kind,
Let me have Thy loving mind

I shall then show forth thy praise,
Serve thee all my happy days;
Then the world shall always see Christ,
The Holy Child in me.

Jesus, Friend of little children, Be a friend to me;
Take my hand and ever keep me close to Thee.

Teach me how to grow in goodness, Daily as I grow;
Thou hast been a child, and surely Thou dost know.

Step by step, O, lead me onward, Upward into youth;
Wiser, stronger, still becoming in Thy truth.

Never leave me, nor forsake me, ever be my Friend;
For I need Thee from life's dawning to its end.

songEN:
Wone m'adehun', O me koma W'ra;
B'ribiara ho nhia me gye sq Wo nko;
Wone m'adwenpa, awia ne 'nadwo,
Nna mų o sxre mų o, Wone me hann no.

Wone me nyansa, ne me nokwasqm;
Wo ne me wx hx daa, m'Awurade;
Wone m'Agya pa, na meyq Wo ba,
Wote me mu na me ne Wo yq k'ro.

Mempq ahonya, ne nnipa nkamfo;
Wone m'apqgyade, bere nyinaa,
Wo na Wudi kan wx me koma' mu,
Xsro Hen kqse, m'ademude neW'.

Xs'ro Hen' kqse, sq midi nim a
Ma minnya xs'ro dqw, O s'ro wia pa;
Me komam koma, nea 'besi biara
Wone m'adehun', O ade ny'naa W'ra.

Ma me ne Wo nnantew, Nyame,
Sq Henok nnantew tete no;
Sx me nsa mmerqw yi mu den;
Na Wo ne me nni nkxmmx pa;
Sq mintumi nhu kwan no a,
Yesu, ma me ne Wo nnante.

Me nko merentumi nnantew,
Ahum no ano yq den wim',
Wxasunsum me af'ri apem,
Atamfo apem retqw me,
Dwudwo po abufuw ano;
Wura, ma me ne Wo nnantew.

Sq me nsa yi sx Wo mu a,
'Ha dqw nyinaa mimmu no hwee;
Metu me kwan aboxd'ru mu
Asqnnua no frankaa n'ase;
Kosi sq mehu Sion apon,
'Gyenkwa, ma me ne Wo nnantew.

Momfa nnxbae dwom mm'ra fie,
Wxaboa nnxbae ny'naa ano,
Ansa na 'pqb're adu;
Yqn Bxfo Nyankopxn no
Ma yqn nea ehia yqn ny'naa;
Mommra Onyankopxn fie
Na monto nnxbae ho dwom!

Yqyq Nyame afuw a,
Yqsow N'ayeyi aba;
Wogu awi pa ne wųra
Enyin ma dqw anaa yaw;
Ahaban ne bqtem pue
Afei qyq awi pa;
Afuw Wura, yqsrq Wo,
Ma yqnyq aba pa nko!

Yqn Nyankopxn no bqba
De Ne nnxbae akx fie;
Da no Obeyi bxne
Ny'naa afi N'afuw no mu;
Xbqhyq N'abxfo ma
Wxahyew aba bxne no;
Na wxde awi pa no
Akogu N'asan so daa.

Wo nkonim asafo bra
Bqto otwab're ho dwom;
Wxaboa nnxbae ny'naa ano
Afi yaw ne bxne mu;
Wxatew wxn ho kosi daa,
Wxbqtra Nyame fie daa,
Abxfo mpem du, mommra
Momfa 'nuonyam nnxbae mm'ra.

N'adebx mu aba no nti, Yqda N'ase;
Amanaman akyqde nti, Yqda N'ase;
Mfuwdx, adedua ne 'twa nti,
Ade nyin b'rč a nnipá ada ne
'Hiade a 'sase akōra nti Yqda N'ase.

Dwumadi ho katua pa mu, Ne pq nyq hx;
Mmoá a yqde ma yqn yxnko mu, Ne pq nyq hx;
Asodė a qda yqn so sq
Yqboa wxn a kxm de wxn ne
'W'rqhowfo, ne nnxbae kyq mu, Ne pq nyq hx.

Ne Honhom nnxbae twa no nti, Yqda N'ase;
Nnipa ny'naa 'pqgyade no nti Yqda N'ase;
'Nwanwade a qbx yqn hu,
Nokwar' a qma yqn 'hodw'ri,
Nea 'kyqn so, 'dx a ahu yqn nti, Yqda N'ase.

songTWI:
For the fruits of His creation, thanks be to God;
For the gifts to every nation, thanks be to god;
For the plowing, sowing, reaping,
Silent growth while men are sleeping,
Future needs in earth's safe keeping, thanks be to God!

In the just reward of labor, God's will is done;
In the help we give our neighbor, God's will is done;
In our worldwide task of caring
For the hungry and despairing,
In the harvests men are sharing, God's will is done.

For the harvests of His Spirit, thanks be to God;
For the good all men inherit, thanks be to God;
For the wonders that astounds us,
For the truths that still confound us,
Most of all, that love has found us, thanks be to God!

songEN:
Yqde yqn koma, nsa Ne nne da Nyame ase,
Wayq anwanwade, Wiase di 'h'rusi Ne mu.
Efi yqn nanom nsam Na Xde akyqde
Ahy'ra yqn, yqn kwan so N'Xda so yq yqn de.

'Yamyefo Nyankopxn Xnka yqn ho daa nyinaa;
Xmfa ahotx kronn Ne dqw nhyq yq komam' daa;
Xnkōra yqn Ne dom mu Onnyaw yqn 'hohia mu;
Onyi yqn mfi mmusum', Seesei ne daa nyinaa.

Nkamfo ne aseda N-ka Agya Nyankopxn
Xba ne Nea Xne Wxn bom di hene s'ro no.
Daa Nyankopxn k'ro a 'Sase ne s'ro som No;
Kan no na qte saa Na qbqyq saa daa.

Yqdxw afuw na yegu aba pa nso wx so;
Nanso Nyame nsa kqse na egugu so nsu;
Xtx suky'rqmmá awxw b're, ne hyew de mā aba fi
Xma mframa ne awia ne nsu a edwudwo.

Nnyeso
Nnepa a yqwx ny'naa
Yenya fi xsoro;
O, monna Aw'rade ase
Ne dx ny'naa ho.

Xno nko ne Xyqfo ma ade ny'naa ara;
Osiesie kwankyqn nhwiren ma nwumm're ns'romma hy'rqn,
Qpo ne mframa tie No, Xma nnomaa aduan',
Yqn a yqyq Ne mma yi, Xma yqn daa aduan.

O, Agya, yqda W'ase, Wx nneqma pa ny'naa ho;
Ogu b're ne otwa b're, Yqn nkwa ne yqn aduan';
Gye nea yqde remaW' yi wo dx akyqde nti;
Na nea Wohwehwq tit'riw, Yqn aseda koma.

songTWI:
Father, we thank you for the light that shines all the day;
For the bright sky you have given most like your heaven;
Father, we thank you.

Father, we thank you for the lamps that lighten the way;
For human skill's exploration of your creation
Father, we thank you.

Father, we thank you for the friends who brighten our play;
For your command to call others sisters and brothers;
Father, we thank you.

Father, we thank you for your love in Jesus today,
Giving us hope for tomorrow through joy and sorrow;
Father, we thank you.

songEN:
'W'rade, fa me dommum, Na manya 'hofadi;
Ma mennyae me nkrantq mu na Mayq nkonimdifo;
Memem xbra haw mu, B're a me nko gyina;
Yq me deduani Wo basam' Na me nsa ayq den.

Me koma yq mmerqw Kosi sq ebehu 'W'ra;
Enni nnyinaso pintinn bi, Ehinhim b're nyinaa.
Entumi ntu 'nammxn, Gye sq Woasane no;
Fa Wo dx no fa no dommum Na adi hen' nkwan' daa.

Me pq nyqm' de kosi Sq qbqyq Wo de;
Sq ebenya 'henni tebeā a Gye sq egyaw n'ahenkyqw.
Ebegyina pintin, Wx ap're p're no mu,
B're a qbqtwer' Wo kokom Nā anya ne nkwa Wo mu.

songTWI:
Make me a captive, Lord, and then I shall be free;
Force me to render up my sword, and I shall conqueror be.
I sink in life's alarms when by myself I stand;
Imprison me within Thine arms, and strong shall be my hand.

My heart is weak and poor till it a master find;
It has no spring of action sure-it varies with the wind.
It cannot freely move till Thou hast wrought its chain;
Enslave it with Thy matchless love, and deathless it shall reign.

My will is not my own till Thou hast made it Thine;
If it would reach a monarch's throne it must its crown resign;
It only stands unbent, amid the clashing strife,
When on Thy bosom it as leant and found in Thee its life.

Not I, but Christ, to honored, loved, exalted;
Not I, but Christ, to seen, be known, be heard;
Not I, but Christ, in every look and action,
Not I, but Christ, in every thought and word.

Not I, but Christ, to gently soothe in sorrow,
Not I, but Christ, to wipe the falling tear;
Not I, but Christ, to lift the weary burden,
Not I, but Christ, to hush away all fear.

Christ, only Christ! No idle words e'er falling,
Christ, only Christ; no needless bustling sound;
Christ, only Christ, no self important bearing;
Christ, only Christ, no trace of "I" be found.

Not I, but Christ, my every need supplying,
Not I, but Christ, my strength and health to be;
Christ, only Christ, for body, soul, and spirit,
Christ, only Christ, here and eternally.

songEN:
Yesu koma mu hx, Xdx wx hx maw'
Xdx a qyq kronn, Na qyq knkwar';
Dqn nti na wo nko nam Hwehwq yxnko yi,
B'rč anika pii wx Yesu komam' hx?

Yesu adwen mu no Osusu wo ho;
Qhyerqn sq owia; Yq dqw sq bosu;
Dqn nti na Wusuro Na wodwennwen saa?
B'rč a Yesu dwen wxn a Watx wxn ho yi?

Yesu afuw mu hx 'Dwuma wx hx maw'
Adwumā a abxfo Pre sq wxbqyq;
Dqn nti na w'ani haw, B'rč a 'dwuma wx hx
Na Yesu rehwehwq 'Paafo N'afuwm' yi?

Yesu soro fie hx Trabea wx hx maw';
'Nuonyam ne dqw wx hx, 'Somdwoe nso sx hx,
Dqn nti na wonam sq Xkobxfo yi,
B'rč a Yesu fie hx Wx trabea ma wo?

songTWI:
In the heart of Jesus there is love for you,
Love most pure and tender, love most deep and true;
Why should you be lonely, why for friendship sigh,
When the heart of Jesus has a full supply?

In the mind of Jesus there is though for you,
Warm as summer sunshine, sweet as morning dew;
Why should you be fearful, why take anxious thought,
Since the mind of Jesus cares for those He bought?

In the fields of Jesus there is work for you;
Such as even angels might rejoice to do;
Why stand idly sighing for some lifework grand,
While the field of Jesus seeks your reaping hand?

In the Index of Jesus there's a place for you;
Glorious, bright, and joyous, calm and peaceful too;
Why then, like a wanderer, Roam with weary pace,
If the Index of Jesus holds for you a place?

songEN:
Kristo, yqne Wo yq adwuma no,
Ewom yqyq mm'rqw ne Bxneyqfo;
Yqde yqn 'de ny'naa maW',
Yqtč ase ma Wo nko,
Wo dom mu yqadi nim Y'adwumayqm'.

Yqne W' yq adwuma Mmorxn hun' so,
Yetutu anammxn, Sq Wo de no;
Yqfrq ahiafo ba Ma 'dedamfikyi so
Bx mmxden gye akra Y'adwumayqm'.

'Gyenkwa, yqmmrq da wx Y'adwumayqm';
Yqn suahun' horow ny' naa Nn'ru Wo de no;
Yqn w'rqkyekye ne sq Wo dom dxxso ma yqn;
Yqn brq dan anigye Y'adwumayqm'.

'Nti momma yqnko so Y'adwumayqm'
Kosi sq yqbqgye Bxne wiase' i;
Kosi sq akra ny'naa Bqgye W' akamfo
Aka yqn ho daapem Y'adwumayqm'.

Mm'rč a qte sqq yim', wuhia 'Gyenkwa,
Mm'rč a qte sqq yim', wuhia sqkyq!
Hu no yie sq, hu no yie sq,
Wo sqkyq no atim Botan no mu!

Nnyeso
Botan ne Yesu, yin qyq 'No;
Botan ne Yesu, Xno nkutoo;
Hu no yie sq, Hu no yie sq,
Wo sqkyq no atim Botan no mu!

Mm'rč a qte sqq yim' wuhia Ky'rqw no;
Mm'rč a qte sqq yim' O, nyq 'nihaw;
Hu no yie sq, hu no yie sq,
Wo sqkyq no atim Botan no mu.

Mm'rč a qte sqq yim' mewx 'Gyenkwa,
Mm'rč a qte sqq yim' mewx sqkyq;
Minim yie sq, minim yie sq,
Me sqkyq no atim Botan no mu!

Nnyeso ma 3
Botan ne Yesu, yiw, qyq 'No;
Botan ne Yesu, Xno nkutoo;
Minim yie sq, minim yie sq,
Me sqkyq no atim Botan no mu!

Ahenni no ba, dqn nti na wotx nko?
Na woreba b'rč a woreyq adu fie?
Nyane, sxre, na fa w'akotade hyq;
Yq ntqm, na mmere retwam kx hyewhyew.

Ahenni no ba,dqn nti na wotwentwqn?
Akatua pa anim na wotwqn yi?
Sxr', boaboa wo ho na 'Gyenkwa no reba;
Yq ntqm na kohyia No kwan wx ewin.

'Sase so aman nyinaa redi ako
Ehu akita wxn, wxatx beraw;
Tie sq teaseqnam no nne rewosow ba,
Ahenni no ba, n-twentwqn bi-o.

N-tra asase nnaadaa hunu yi mu,
Hwq sqnea n'anuonyam no retwan kx;
Bubu atamfo mpokyerq dennen nom',
Ahenni no ba, dan wo ho fi ho.

Ma w'ani nhwq faako na ma wo ti so;
Hwq Xhen' a Xreba no 'nuonyam;
Hwq! hann repue wx mmepx no atifi;
'Henni no mma, monnye mō ani nto dwom.

songTWI:
Heir of the kingdom, O why dost slumber?
Why art thou sleeping so near thy blest Index?
Wake thee, arouse thee, and gird on thine armor,
Speed, for the moments are hurrying on.

Heir of the kingdom, say, why does thou linger?
How canst thou tarry in sight of the prize?
Up, and adorn thee, the Savior is coming;
Haste to receive Him descending the skies.

Earth's mighty nations, in strife and commotion,
Tremble with terror, and sink in dismay;
Listen, 'tis nought but the chariot's loud rumbling;
Heir of the kingdom, no longer delay.

Stay not, O stay not for earth's vain allurements!
See how its glory is passing away;
Break the strong fetters the foe that bound o'er thee;
Heir of the kingdom, turn, turn thee away.

Keep the eye single, the head upward lifted;
Watch for the glory of earth's coming King;
Lo! o'er the mountaintops light is now breaking;
Heirs of the kingdom, rejoice ye and sing.

Watch, ye saints, with eyelids waking;
Lo! the powers of heaven are shaking;
Keep your lamps all trimmed and burning,
Ready for your Lord's returning.

Refrain
Lo! he comes, lo!Jesus comes; Lo!
He comes, He comes all glorious!
Jesus comes to reign victorious, Lo!
He comes, yes, Jesus comes!

Lo! the promise of your Savior,
Pardoned sin and purchased favor,
Blood-washed robes and crowns of glory;
Haste to tell redemption's story.

Kingdoms at their base are crumbling,
Hark! His chariot wheels are rumbling;
Tell, O tell of grace abounding,
While the seventh trump is sounding.

Nations wane, though proud and stately;
Christ His kingdom hasteneth greatly;
Earth her latest pasts is summing;
Shout, ye saints, your Lord is coming.

Sinners, come, while Christ is pleading;
Now for you He's interceding;
Haste, ere grace and time diminished
Shall proclaim the mystery finished.

songEN:
Kristoni, nnye w'ahome,
To w'ahom'gye adwen gu;
Wugyina dxm mfimfini;
Wqn, bx mpae!

Fa wo s'ro akode hyq,
Hyq no 'nadwo ne awia;
Xbxne no retqw wo;
Wqn, bx mpae!

Tie wxn a wxadi nkonim;
Wxhyq 'kofo kwan 'gyirae;
Wxn ny'naa de nne dqdq teqm;
"Wqn, bx mpae!"

Tit'riw no, tie w'Aw'rade,
Wo kxn dx sq wutie No;
Fa N'asqm sie wo komam;
"Wqn bx mpae!"

Wqn te sqnea qno nko
Na nkonim no gyina so;
Srq sq mmoa fi s'ro bqba;
"Wqn, bx mpae!"

songTWI:
Christian, seek not yet repose,
Cast thy dreams of ease away;
Thou art in the midst of foes;
Watch and pray!

Gird thy heavenly armor on,
Wear it ever, night and day;
Ambushed lies the evil one;
Watch and pray!

Hear the victors who o'er came;
Still they mark each warrior's way;
All with one sweet voice exclaim:
"Watch and pray!"

Hear, above all, hear thy Lord,
Him thou lovest to obey;
Hide within thy heart His word:
"Watch and pray!"

Watch, as if on that alone
Hung the issue of the day;
Pray that help may be sent down;
Watch and pray!

We know not the hour of the Master's appearing;
Yet signs all foretell that the moment is nearing
When He shall return 'tis the promise most cheering
But we know not the hour.

Refrain
He will come, let us watch and be ready;
He will come, hallelujah! hallelujah!
He will come in the clouds of His Father's
Bright glory but we know not the hour.

There's light for the wise who are seeking salvation;
There's truth in the book of the Lord's revelation;
Each prophecy points to the great comsummation
But we know not the hour.

We'll watch and we'll pray,
with our lamps trimmed and burning;
We'll work and we'll wait till the Master's returning;
We'll sing and rejoice, every omen discerning
But we know not the hour.

O Christian, awake! 'tis the Master's command;
With helmet and shield, and a sword in thy hand,
To meet the bold tempter, go, fearlessly go,
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

Refrain
Stand like the brave, stand like the brave,
Stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

The cause of thy Master with vigor defend;
Be watchful, be zealous, and fight to the end;
Wherever He leads thee, go, valiantly go,
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

Press on, never doubting, thy Captain is near,
With grace to supply, and with comfort to cheer;
His love, like a stream in the desert will flow;
Then stand like the brave, with thy face to the foe.

songEN:
Kristo nsraafo, monkx Sqnea mokx sa,
Yesu asqnnua no Momfa nni anim.
Xsahen' Kristo di Yqn anim tia dxm;
Monkx akonim hx, Ne frankaa rekx.

Nnyeso
Kristo nsraafo, monkx Sqnea mokx sa;
Yesu asqnnua no Momfa nni anim.

Nyame asafo no, Kx sq dxm kqse;
Kristofo, yqnenam Nea treneefo fae;
Mpaapaemu nni yqn mu, na yqyq biako,
Biako wx asqnkam', 'nidasom' ne dxm.

Nhenkyqw, nhengua asqe, 'Henni hwe ase,
Yesu asafo de Ebetim hx daa;
Asaman apon mpo Remmu mfa so da;
Yqwx Kristo bxhyq a enni huammx.

Yaanom, monkx anim, Momfra yqn kuw yim',
Mo ne yqn nyinaa mmom Nto nkonimdi dwom;
Anuonyam ne 'nidi Nka Xhen Kristo,
Eyi na abxfo Ne nnipa to daa.

Fa w'ahoxden no ko ko pa
Kristo ne w'ahoxden nifa;
Sx abrabx pa no mu yie
Qbqyqw' ahenkyqw daapem.

Nyame dom mu tu mm'rika pa,
Ma w'ani so na hwq N'anim;
N'kwa ne ne kwan da w'anim;
Kristo ne kwan ne akyqde.

Faw' dadwen to wo Hwqfo so,
Twer' No n'Obehu wo mmxfx;
Twer' No, na wo kra behu sq
Kristo ne ne nkwa ne ne dx.

M-pa aba na Xbqn wo;
Xnsakra da, wo som No bo;
Wo de gye di na wubehu
Sq Kristo ne w'ade nyinaa.

songTWI:
Fight the good fight with all thy might,
Christ is thy strength and Christ thy right;
Lay hold on life and it shall be
Thy joy and crown eternally.

Run the straight race through God's good grace;
Lift up thine eyes, and seek His face.
Life with its path before us lies;
Christ is the way, and Christ the prize.

Cast care aside, lean on thy guide;
His boundless mercy will provide;
Trust, and the trusting soul shall prove
Christ is its life, and Christ its love.

Faint not, nor fear, His arms are near;
He changeth not and thou art dear.
Only believe, and thou shalt see
That Christ is all in all to thee.

songEN:
Me kra, trqw wo ntaban mu;
Hwehwq wo kyqfa pa n'
Fi nneqma a etwam ho,
Kx s'ro wo trabea hx;
'Wia, xsram ne ns'romma kx,
B're beyi 'sase yi hx;
Sxr' me kra, yq ntqm kxtra
Xs'ro agua no so.

Nsuten sen kxbx po mu
Qntra n'akwan so daa;
Ogya tų a, qkx 'wia nkyqn;
Wxkx nea wofi hx;
'Krā a xyq Nyame de nso
Kxn dx sq ohu N'anim,
Xp're kx nea Xte no
Kxhome Ne kokom'.

'Kwantufo munnni yaw bio,
Monkx 'kyqde no ho;
Yqn 'Gyenkwa no reba ntqm,
Nkonimdi mu wx wim;
Munnim sq aka kakra
Na wxabue 'nigye kwan no,
Yebegyaw yqn 'w'rqhow ny'naa
Fi fam ha akx 's'ro.

songTWI:
Rise, my soul, and stretch thy wings,
Thy better portion trace;
Rise from transitory things
Toward heaven, thy native place:
Sun, and moon, and stars decay;
Time shall soon this earth remove;
Rise, my soul, and haste away
To seats prepared above.

Rivers to the ocean run,
Nor stay in all their course;
Fire ascending seeks the sun;
Both speed them to their source;
So a soul that's born of God,
Longs to view His glorious face,
Forward tends to His abode
To rest in His embrace.

Cease, ye pilgrims, cease to mourn;
Press onward to the prize;
Soon our Savior will return,
Triumphant in the skies;
Yet a season, and you know
Happy entrance will be given,
All our sorrows left below,
And earth exchanged for heaven.

Lord of all good, our gifts we bring You now;
Use them Your holy purpose to fulfill.
Tokens of love and pledges they shall be
That our whole life is offered to Your will.

We give our minds to understand Your ways;
Hands, voices, eyes to serve Your great design;
Hearts with the flame of your own love ablaze:
Thus for Your glory all our pow'rs combine.

Father, whose bounty all creation shows;
Christ, by whose willing sacrifice we live;
Spirit, from whom all life in fullness flows:
To You with grateful hearts ourselves we give.

songEN:
Yqn agyanom Nyame a Wo tumi nsa
Ky'rq nsase horow a 'yq fq no kwan;
Nsoromma hyqnhyqn no kwan wx ewim,
Yqn nnaase nnwom ba W'ahengua anim.

Wo dx aky'rq yqn kwan mm're a atwam,
'Sase a Wode ma yqn kwa yi so;
Bqyq yqn Sodifo ne Kwanky'rqfo.
W'asqm ne yqn mm'ra, W'akwan, yqn akwan.

Bx yqn ho ban fi ko ne yar'dxm mu,
Fa Wo tumi nsa no bx yqn ho ban;
Fa Wo nokwar' som no hyq yqn komam';
Ma Wo nnepa no nsiesie yqn 'somdwoem'

Kanyan Wo nk'rxfo yqn brq kwan no so,
Di yqn anim fi sum mu kx 'dekyeem'
Fa xsoro dx ne dom hyq yqn ma;
Na 'nuonyam ne nkamfo nyq Wo de daa.

Nyame a Wo din da adasa so;
Wo a Wo dom apam no tim hx daa,
Ka baanu a wxtwqn W'anim yi ho;
Trqw 'dx a wxrehyira so no mu.

Ma wxn nkabom no nhyira afof'ro;
Ma wommue wxn apon mma ahxho,
Ma wxn ntease a ayamye wx mu,
Fa adwen a 'mu da hx hyira wxn.

Yi pqsqmenkominya fi wxn mu;
Fa kasa mu nokwaredi dom wxn.
Ma nkabom no nnyina wx ap'rep're
Ne 'sase so ha nsakrae biara mu.

Xbra akwantu no fa biara mu,
Ma wxnkae bx a wxhyq no nnq yi;
Ma Wo Honhom nky'rq wxn kwan baabiara,
Na wxn dx nnyina Kristom' gyidi so.

songTWI:
Let all mortal flesh keep silence,
and with fear and trembling stand;
ponder nothing earthly-minded,
for with blessing in his hand,
Christ our God to earth descendeth,
